the 'zk app' community (of which I consider myself a part) frequently overcomplicates things

simple mechanisms are often how technologies reach adoption (think of the AMM as the starting point for dexes)

{membership proof + arbitrary sig}  circuit (i.e. sapir-ecdsa https://github.com/personaelabs/sapir) is our AMM

you can make any interesting identity statement as a composition of different membership proofs

it's why we (personae) have focused so intensely on making this circuit extremely performant in client-side settings

it's powerful enough that we don't even need to disclaim that 'zk' is used in creddd.xyz

rather than build a VM 'top-down', our ambition is to build a new reputation VM 'bottom-up' via membership proofs

this is a path that is much more compatible with product growth in the real world

have been working on the set of ideas around 'zk-identity' for years now (semaphore -> to writing heyanon -> to nouns nymz -> creddd). 

insofar as many shots on goal may have taught me anything, it's that overcomplicating the first 'wedge' is a huge mistake
